boolean isEmpty()
Determines whether a queue is empty. Precondition: None. Postcondition: Returns true if the queue is empty; otherwise returns false.

size

int size()
Determines the length of a queue. Precondition: None. Postcondition: Returns the number of items that are currently in the queue. Throws: None.

dequeueAll

void dequeueAll()
Removes all items of a queue. Precondition: None. Postcondition: The queue is empty.

peek

java.lang.Object peek()
                      throws queues.QueueException
Retrieves the item at the front of a queue. Precondition: None. Postcondition: If the queue is not empty, the item that was added to the queue earliest is returned. If the queue is empty, the operation is impossible and QueueException is thrown.

Throws:
queues.QueueException

enqueue

void enqueue(java.lang.Object item)
             throws queues.QueueException
Adds an item at the back of a queue. Precondition: item is the item to be inserted. Postcondition: If the operation was successful, newItem is at the back of the queue. Some implementations may throw QueueException if item cannot be added to the queue.

Throws:
queues.QueueException

dequeue

java.lang.Object dequeue()
                         throws queues.QueueException
Retrieves and removes the front of a queue. Precondition: None. Postcondition: If the queue is not empty, the item that was added to the queue earliest is returned and the item is removed. If the queue is empty, the operation is impossible and QueueException is thrown.

Throws:
queues.QueueException
